posts.name: Hemant Singh
posts.ques: What is the darkest part of a software engineer’s career?
posts.answer:
1.You are nothing more than a money making machine for any company.  
 
 2. If you sit on the chair for a long time, your back becomes crooked or your mother dies while working or you die, it does not make any sense to the company, company only wants productivity.  
 
 3. Whether you are a manager, chief technical officer, or any position, you are just a resource. And the health of the resource does not matter much and when it is no longer fit for use, it is replaced.  
 
 4. When it's time to spend money for your children's education, your career is on the decline stage.  
 
 5. You must always be ready to change jobs at any day, any time. 
 
 Thank you for reading.
